        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-11T14:39:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This tells me that you’ve used /SUBSYSTEM:WINDOWS (which I’ll verify a few files from now, I guess).\n\nWe should be using /SUBSYSTEM:CONSOLE (and this line should be wmain()), specifically for tests. We want to leave stderr hooked up to the console so that any messages that the handler logs are visible during the test. /SUBSYSTEM:WINDOWS defeats that.\n\nI suspect that you may have been misled by the freaky build that we use for crashpad_handler.exe: we build crashpad_handler.exe (which has both wWinMain() and wmain()) with /SUBSYSTEM:WINDOWS. But then we take that and transform it with editbin to produce crashpad_handler.com, which is /SUBSYSTEM:CONSOLE. Tests wind up using crashpad_handler.com and never crashpad_handler.exe, so they’re using the console version with messages logged to stderr going someplace visible, where we want them.",
      "revId": "5c2fa9c328502d17f18f8e9b77f12aa883d3dfe6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
